jacdac.DmxCmd.Send:
Argument: channels bytes. Send a DMX packet, up to 236bytes long, including the start code.
* ```
const [channels] = jdunpack<[Buffer]>(buf, "b")
```
jacdac.DmxReg.Enabled:
Read-write bool (uint8_t). Determines if the DMX bridge is active.
* ```
const [enabled] = jdunpack<[number]>(buf, "u8")
```
modules.DmxClient: A service that can send DMX512-A packets with limited size. This service is designed to allow tinkering with a few DMX devices, but only allows 235 channels. More about DMX at https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DMX512.
modules.DmxClient.enabled: Determines if the DMX bridge is active.
modules.DmxClient.send: Send a DMX packet, up to 236bytes long, including the start code.
modules.DmxClient.setEnabled: Determines if the DMX bridge is active.
